We're still working hard to get power restored to customers impacted by this fault.

Our engineers have been working around the clock since the storm hit our network earlier on in the weekend, and throughout the last 24 hours have been able to get power back on to a large number of areas. The damage to our network is severe and, in some cases, our engineers are needing to rebuild whole parts of the network which is why it's taken so long to get your power back on. We know some customers have been without power for some time now but we promise we're doing everything in our power to get things sorted sooner. The best place to keep track of live updates is right here on PowerTrack, and this will be the fastest way to get the latest information about your power cut - it's updated in real time, so if you register for updates here, you'll get notified the moment anything changes.

If you're struggling at all or have any medical concerns without electricity, please call us on 105 and a member of the team will be happy to help.

Once again, we're so sorry for the power cut and will do everything we can to fix this as quickly and safely as possible. Thank you so much for your patience and support while we work to get your power back on.
